cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.HC 

The paper discusses learning to collaborate in visually rich environments, which involves both perception and communication. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of AI2-THOR, a simulation platform for AI research, suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of learning to collaborate also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it requires agents to act in the physical world. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of communication in collaboration, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
